Incident.Summary: RAPID / Operating and advertising without an ADR license by posting "Buy Junk Car" signs.

IncidentAddress.IncAddrComment: Signs posted in several different locations

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
23-MSP-029029757 Transportation Article 15 / ADR violations by posting "Buy Junk Cars" signs.

   On August 14, 2023, I, Corporal Jean L. Davenport #4718, MPS PCSD/RAPID, began an investigation into TA 15-502 violations after receiving a tip from a licensed dealer reporting a possible unlicensed person operating as an Automotive Dismantler and Recycler.


    
    On August 21, 2023, I received another tip from a licensed Automotive Dismantler reporting a possible unlicensed subject advertising: "CA$H FOR CARS All Makes and Models FREE TOWING 443-805-1952, and sign is posted in Maryland.



   
    Another tip I received shows a sign posted on a telephone pole on Erdman Avenue, "CASH FOR CARS" ANY MAKE... 443-503, however, I am unable to make out the telephone number.




On September 19, 2023, I received a tip and photos of signs posted on the corner of Ritchie Highway and 5th Avenue in Glen Burnie, MD:


     This case is open pending follow up and further investigation to determine the name(s) associated with the phone numbers.

SUPPLEMENT:

On September 25, 2023, I received two (2) more tips on "Buy Junk Cars" advertisement seen in and/or near Maryland roadways:




     This investigation involves tips received by the RAPID Unit for "Buy Junk Car" signs posted in Anne Arundel County, Baltimore County, and Baltimore City, and in violation of Transportation Article Title 15-502 (a) & (b):

§ 15-502. License required

(a) In general. -- A person may not conduct the business of an automotive dismantler and recycler or a scrap processor, or engage in the business of acquiring or offering to purchase or remove vehicles which are to be dismantled in whole or in part by that person for the sale of usable parts, unless the person is licensed by the Administration under this subtitle.
(b) Advertisements. --
(1) A person may not advertise for the purchase, towing, or removal of junk or abandoned vehicles unless the person is licensed by the Administration under this subtitle.
(2) Any advertisement for the purchase, towing, or removal of junk or abandoned vehicles by a licensee under this subtitle shall include the license number of the licensee.

     None of the eight (8) signs posted have an ADR License number on the sign as required by TA 15-502 (b)(2).  I conducted an investigative search for the telephone numbers listed on the signs and obtained the following information:

1.  443-449-8814 - Dylan Thomas Etchison, DOB 08/08/1997, 3015 Delaware Avenue, Halethorpe, MD 21227 / dylan21227@gmail.com
                               dba D & D Junk Car Buyers
2.  443-805-1952 - Darin N. Johnson, DOB 10/11/1965, 1104 Snowden Pond Road, Laurel, MD 20708 / anedi90@yahoo.com & ane di@yahoo.com / Glen Davis of Car Junkies LLC.
3.  443-503-9820 - Alexander Scott Pappas, DOB 10/11/1962, 7613 Chestnut Avenue, Fort Howard, MD 21052 / apappas7787@gmail.com
4.  443-962-4413 - Robert L. Petree, DOB 03/21/1951, 502 Stoney Hill Court, Odenton, MD 2113 / dvd8720@yahoo.com & robertpetree@gmail.com
5.  443-500-6779 - Diamond Brady Johnson, DOB 04/02/1974, 914 Edgerly Road, Glen Burnie, MD 21060 / diamond.johnson11@aol.com
6.  443-962-4413 - Also Robert L. Petree (same as #4)
7.  410-456-9433 - Vehicle tag 7CG1148 with "Cruisin for Cars" sign on back window comes back to a frequent driver of Rebecca Elizabeth Purdie, DOB 04/28/1980.
8.  443-707-9812 - Dreivin R. Chacon, DOB 06/27/1990, 3729 Brooklyn Avenue, Brooklyn, MD 21225 and Tiera Brooks, DOB 02/27/1994, 3601 Silver Park Drive, Baltimore, MD 20746
                               dba DC Towing and Transport / dreivinchacon@gmail.com
9.  443-356-1827 - Dwight Hammond (investigated under separate case number)
   
    On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1100 hours, I spoke via telephone with Dylan Etchison who acknowledged he had posted signs to buy junk cars.  I provided him information on the ADR violations and emailed information on obtaining an ADR license through MDOT.  Dylan advised he was in the process of getting a shop to conduct his towing business and agreed to take his signs down until he obtains a license.  

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1109 hours, I contacted Darin Johnson via telephone and left a message.  His professionally made yellow and blue sign was posted near Hawkins Point by the Royal Farms.  This phone number was later answered by Glen Davis as detailed below.

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1130 hours, I contacted Robert L. Petree and spoke to him via telephone.  He advised it was his Uncle Mike Williams signs and using Petree's phone number.  Petree agreed to take the signs down within the next two (2) weeks.  I advised Petree two (2) of the ads were posted on a sign post on Ritchie Highway along with a sign for buying campers.  Petree commented the guy is buying campers and reselling the campers.  Petree did not know the camper guy's name or know Diamond Cody Johnson.  Petree does not have an email address, therefore, I text messaged him the information on how to obtain an ADR license. 

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1144 hours, I contacted Diamond Brady Johnson via telephone and left a message; the voicemail message on this number referenced buying cars.  I received a voicemail message back from Mr. Johnson; "...this is Used Cars and Trailer, please give me a call back at 443-500-6779, to schedule an appointment to look at your car or trailer..." 

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1149 hours, I contacted Craig Michael Bundy via telephone and left a message.  I attempted a second call with negative results.  I then forwarded an email with information to bundo22b@yahoo.com reference the sign posted on the back window of a black 2012 Chrysler Caravan with Maryland Registration 7CG1148.  An Etix search of this registration shows the vehicle was stopped three (3) times and each time the driver was identified as Rebecca Elizabeth Purdie, DOB 04/28/1980 / MD C-250-152-729-502. 

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1305 hours, I contacted Dreivin R. Chacon of DC Towing who acknowledged he had magnetic signs posted on his tow truck to buy junk cars.  He stated he would cooperate and take them off until he obtained an ADR license.  He provided me with an email address of dreivinchacon@gmail.com and I forwarded him information on the violation and how to obtain and ADR license.  

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1315 hours, I contacted Diamond Brady Johnson via telephone.  He acknowledged he purchased used cars.  When I informed Diamond Johnson of the purpose of my call, he became irate and hung up on me.  I then called back, and he advised he was driving and would not provide me any further information and then provided me with a fake address.  I located and email address for Diamond Johnson and forwarded information to diamond.johnson11@aol.com.  

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1400 hours, I contacted Alexander Pappas Sr. via telephone and left him a message.  I then forwarded an email with information to apappas7787@gmail.com.

     On Wednesday, September 27, 2023, at approximately 1430 hours, I made contact with Glen Davis of Car Junkies LLC.  His phone number, 443-805-1952, is posted on the professional yellow and blue sign located at Hawkins Point by Royal Farms.  Davis advised his driver's put the signs out, and he would have them pick-up the signs as soon as possible.  He stated he has a storefront located at 10451 Mill Run Circle, Owings Mills, MD 21117, and he has a Trader's License issued for his business and would apply for an ADR license.  I forwarded him information on the violation and link to MVA to obtain an ADR license.

    On Monday, October 2, 2023, I received another tip of a sign located at the corner of Mountain Road and Outing Avenue in Pasadena, the sign reads "Up to $300 for Junk Cars 443-356-1827."  I immediately recognized the phone number from previous encounters with Dwight Hammond.  Hammond has been charged with Title 15 violations three (3) times already; Talbot, Dorchester, and Wicomico Counties.  This incident will be assigned a separate RMS case number.  

    On Tuesday, October 3, 2023, at approximately 1330 hours, I called the phone number included on the "Cruisin For Cars" ad on back of a Chrysler van; 410-456-9433.  I spoke with a subject who identified himself as Nick and said he would give Rebecca a message to contact me.  He indicated they were getting into the business of buying cars and previously had a car buying license.  

    Case open pending follow up with Diamond Brady Johnson.  The six (6) other persons contacted were cooperative and provided with a verbal warning.  The advertised phone numbers have been added to the RAPID spreadsheet for future reference.

On October 30, 2023, I, Cpl. Jean L. Davenport #4718, MSP PCSD/RAPID, received more tips of signs posted near the exit ramp of Route 100 / Mountain Road & MD 177 in Pasadena, and on Ritchie Hwy by the Double T Diner, Anne Arundel County, Maryland.   I recognized this sign and phone number being associated with Diamond Johnson who has been uncooperative when contacted about the ADR violation.



Transportation Article§15–502.

    (a)    A person may not conduct the business of an automotive dismantler and recycler or a scrap processor, or engage in the business of acquiring or offering to purchase or remove vehicles which are to be dismantled in whole or in part by that person for the sale of usable parts, unless the person is licensed by the Administration under this subtitle.

    (b)    (1)    A person may not advertise for the purchase, towing, or removal of junk or abandoned vehicles unless the person is licensed by the Administration under this subtitle.

        (2)    Any advertisement for the purchase, towing, or removal of junk or abandoned vehicles by a licensee under this subtitle shall include the license number of the licensee.

    (c)    A person may not store on any private property for more than 30 days any vehicle that is to be dismantled, destroyed, or scrapped, unless the person is an automotive dismantler and recycler or a scrap processor licensed under this subtitle.

    (d)    This section does not prohibit an unlicensed person from purchasing, transporting, towing, or removing a vehicle to a licensed automotive dismantler and recycler or a licensed scrap processor for dismantling, destroying, or scrapping.

    (e)    A person convicted of a violation of subsection (a) of this section is subject to:

        (1)    For a first offense, imprisonment not exceeding 6 months or a fine not exceeding $1,000 or both; and

        (2)    For a second or subsequent offense, imprisonment not exceeding 1 year or a fine not exceeding $2,000 or both.



In addition, I received two (2) new tips for "Buy Junk Car" on-line advertisements as follows:

    I checked the RAPID spreadsheet for the phone number 443-938-2775 with negative results.  An internet search for Deals on Wheels and/or Dealz on Wheelz Towing returned an address; 3121 Lohrs Lane, Baltimore, MD 21229, 443-334-6653 and a Facebook page photo of their tow truck "D.O.W." with the same phone number on the truck 443-938-2775, with US DOT 2997801.   A check with CVED on the US DOT Number shows an address of 5520 Whitwood Road, Baltimore, however, the info has not been updated since 2017. 

    On Thursday, November 15, 2023, I met Detective Exdol Williams from Baltimore City and TFC Tucker at 3121 Lohrs Lane, Baltimore, MD, to conducted an educational visit with Deals on Wheels Towing owner identified as Alvin Ray Henry Jr.  Upon further investigation, we found that Deals on Wheels was not operational at this location and possibly be operating a scam where he tows vehicles from individuals and then absconds on paying them for the vehicles.  

    TFC Tucker made a phone call to the advertised phone number and spoke with a person believed to be Alvin Henry who advised he would not pick up a vehicle at the St. Agnes' hospital, but would pick up the vehicle at some other location.  

    From this location, Detective Williams assisted us in a checking other addresses for Deals on Wheels Towing with negative results.  However, while en route to other locations, I identified other Buy Junk Car signs posted on Greenspring and Reisterstown Road and identified the phone number 443-356-1827 on one of the professionally made sign as that of Dwight Hammond who we have charged in the past for ADR violations.


    I then drove to 7382 Maury Road, Windsor Mills, Maryland for an educational visit with Dwight Hammond with negative results.  This address was identified as a recent address for Hammond and the address provided by Hammond to a Caroline County Deputy on a recent traffic stop in Caroline County in October 2023.   I identified several other signs with Hammonds phone number 443-356-1827 in the Reisterstown and Pikesville areas.

   I then drove to 816 Dale Road and 914 Edgerly Road (one street apart) in Glen Burnie to make contact with Diamond Johnson.  The residents at these locations where not familiar with Diamond Johnson.  The 914 Edgerly Drive address appears on Johnson's May 22, 2023 Leads Online transactions and lists a phone number 443-500-6779.

   Through further investigation, Leads Online associated Diamond Johnson with another address 7852 Leymar Road, Glen Burnie.  

    TFC Tucker then contacted 443-500-6779 and inquired about the advertisement posted on Route 2 in Anne Arundel County offering to buy RV's and cars.  TFC Tucker spoke to a subject who identified himself as Tony.  Tony advised that he could possibly pick up the camper in Kent Island and negotiated a price of three (3) to five (5) hundred dollars.  

    Case open pending further investigation.

On November 16, 2023, I observed a yellow and blue professionally made signs advertising CA$H FOR CAR$ All Makes and Model Free Towing 443-805-1952".  Multiple like signs were observed posted around Reisterstown and Pikesville in Baltimore County, Maryland and none of the signs contain an ADR license number as required by law.
     

     On Tuesday, December 5, 2023, I called phone number 443-805-1952 from a MSP landline and left a message.  An internet search for the phone number indicates the number is associated with Darrin Johnson.  I called and left a message with negative results.

     On Wednesday, December 6, 2023, I contacted the above phone number again and left a message.
 
     On Friday, December 8, 2023, I conducted a follow-up to the yellow and blue sign with phone number 443-805-1952 and conducted a TLO and RMS search for the number and both systems associated a name of Darrin Johnson.  TLO has email address for Darrin Johnson that indicated he is or was employed by MVA / MDOT.  RMS Report 17-MSP-044096 lists Darrin Johnson as an employee of MDOT in Silver Springs.    Several messages sent to Darrin Johnson's TLO listed email addresses were returned as undeliverables.  

     On Monday, December 11, 2023, at approximately 1413 hours, I called the number again and left another message; 443-805-1952.

     On Monday, December 11, 2023, I conduced a follow-up to Buy Junk Car Signs posted by Dwight Hammond.  I conducted a Leads Online search and discovered Hammond has not had a transaction since October 18, 2023.  I called Hammond's number 443-356-1827 and left a message for Dwight to take down his signs.

    I received another tip on a Buy Junk Car sign posted by The Dash In at the corner of Mountain Road and Jumpers Hole Road, Pasadena, Anne Arundel County, MD.  An internet search for the listed phone number 202-704-3870, shows association to Rene Arquimides Guevara, 4/2/84, 3529 River Bridge Way, Laurel, MD 20764. 

     On Monday, December 11, 2023, I called 202-704-3870 and spoke with a Hispanic male from G Towing.  He advised he would have his driver take the signs down, and I provided him information on how to get an ADR license.  

     I received another tip for Junk Car Sign on back window of a vehicle at Wendy's drive through, Edwin Raynor Blvd Pasadena, MD.  I had received this sign on a previous tip and made contact with the vehicle owner and educated them on the process to get an ADR license.  I called the number again, 410-456-9433, and spoke to a male who advised "she" was working on getting the lettering peeled off her back window this week and was just going to leave the work "Cruisin".  


   On follow up, I also emailed Alvin Henry from Dealz on Wheelz Towing regarding his Buy Junk Car signs and info on TA 15-502.  I then called 443-938-2775 and spoke with Alvin Henry who advised it wasn't him it was someone else posting on Insta Gram and tagged him in on the ad.  I provided him text and photos of his ads and he advised he would take them down and apply to MVA for an ADR license.

   Case closed / Non-Criminal.
